</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 8:01:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1660.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two Questions...ok maybe a few...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Anything else I can kill in Wakening Land then with a 45 War and 45 Cleric?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There are a number of Dino type mobs outside the entrance to Skyshrine which are pretty easy and should still be blue at level 45.  A warrior and a cleric could take them out easily.  There are also animals in WL which are good exp at that level.<br>
<br>
Another option would be to head to CS and do wyverns.  Of course, you have to compete with all the quad kiters, which can suck at times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Post-o-holic</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 9:41:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1660.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two Questions...ok maybe a few...</span><hr size=1> If you're still 45, you don't have to leave the old world.  A frog in Guk, for example, wasn't meant to deal with being beaten on by Kunark weapons from players in Velious armors.<br>
<br>
City of Mist is amazing at that level.  Endless mobs with low HP and a nice bonus.<br>
<br>
The entrance to The Hole offers a similar reward, but you have snare issues. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utunnelratx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TunnelRatX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/31/02 10:19:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1660.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fearlessblack.net/images/Maulo003.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two Questions...ok maybe a few...</span><hr size=1> City of Mist aye? The thought of low HP mobs is very nice.<br>
<br>
See my semi-longterm goal was to hunt in WL for Quest Gem drops for Thurg armor. As Thurg armor is what is realistically  attainable by our guild currently.<br>
<br>
So I figure I work up my ToV faction by killing giants in GD, so I can bind in Skyshrine so the CR won't be such a pain in WL.<br>
<br>
But is City of Mist is really as awesome as you say then I think I put off the Velious Armor idea for a bit longer.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts on this? I really appreciate the comments so far btw.<br>
<br>
Thanks again,<br>
